title: rukia_moon
body:
ルキア・ムーン

Character from [[Shinrabanshou]]. Introduced in the Shingoku Chapter as a mysterious human girl observing the main character [[maxi_(shinrabanshou)|Maxi]], but is later revealed to be a demon tasked by the last Rashin Emperor to search for his descendant, [[san_morte_(shinrabanshou)|San Morte]]. When she and [[Dirculum]] find Morte in the following Ougarasen Chapter, Rukia wants to protect the her while Dirculum wants to use her as a figurehead and take over the world. Their differences cause Rukia to leave Dirculum's side and join up with Maxi to defeat her.

Rukia goes by the title of Moonlight King, though she has no subordinates or even family, leaving her with the freedom to do whatever she wants. She's old friends with [[shirokarasuou_kurooshe|Kurooshe]] and always butted heads with Dirculum even before the San Morte incident.

Her name is derived from "Lucia", a latin name derived from the word for "light", referencing her title. However, "Moon" is only given as her last name once and may be a false name as part of her human disguise.

h4. Cards:

* Shingoku Part 1: "Rukia Moon":http://www.palusuke.com/list/shingoku1/011.html

* Ougarasen Part 1: "Rashintei San Morte":http://www.palusuke.com/list/ogarasen/opr.html, "Gekkouou Rukia":http://www.palusuke.com/list/ogarasen/o011.html

title: kagari_shuusei
body: [b]Kagari Shuusei (縢 秀星)[/b] is a character from [[Psycho-Pass]], one of the Enforcers in Unit One of the Public Safety Bureau's Criminal Investigation Division. The youngest of the group after [[Tsunemori Akane]], he has been a latent criminal since his early childhood. As a result Kagari seems to not have grown up, and constantly tells jokes and teases people. He also keeps dinsoaur toys and jelly beans on his desk, and is interested in cooking. He is also a very able fighter in hand-to-hand combat, able to easily kill enemies bigger than him. He also harbors a hate for normal society and Sybil, but is loyal to his friends and despises those who would kill others out of a sense of superiority. [spoiler]In episode 16 he witnesses the true nature of Sybil, and is promptly killed by a cyborg under Sybil's control.[/spoiler]

title: karanomori_shion
body: [b]Karanomori Shion (唐之杜 志恩)[/b] is a character from [[Psycho-Pass]], a Latent Criminal working with Unit One as their information analyst. Shion is very good with computer systems and is crucial in assisting Unit One during their investigations. She is frequently seen smoking and enjoys teasing [[Tsunemori Akane]]. [[Kougami Shin'ya]] and [[Kagari Shuusei]] have flatteringly nicknamed her "The Godess of Information Analysis". She is in a relationship with [[Kunizuka Yayoi]].

title: kougami_shin'ya
body: [b]Kougami Shin'ya (狡噛 慎也)[/b] is the main male character of [[Psycho-Pass]], an Enforcer of Unit One. At first seen as a violent man who disposes of anyone deemed a criminal by any means necessary, he is shaken by [[Tsunemori Akane]]'s sense of justice and her using the Dominator against him to prevent him from killing a rape victim deemed a criminal, Kougami changes. A calm and collected man, he is also extremely good at figuring out the threads behind crimes and is frequently the one who solves the cases. He is well built, and is an expert martial artist. He is also quite knowledgeable in literature. After the events of the first episode, he and Akane quickly become somewhat close and care about each other. It is revealed that [spoiler]he was an Inspector in the past alongside Nobuchika Ginoza, but the death of an Enforcer under his command (Sasayama) in a horrible murder led him to obsessing over catching the perpetrator, and as a result of too much insight into criminal minds, he was deemed a Latent Criminal by Sibyl and demoted into an Enforcer. He hates Makishima Shogo for his role in Sasayama's death.[/spoiler].

It responds to voice commands thanks to its built-in advanced micro[[computer]] and can also fire several different types of ammunition, which include sound-suppresed [[bullet]]s, standard bullets, armor piercing bullets, incendiary bullets, full-auto, semi-auto and single-action bullets, 2-shot arc [i]"Double Wavy"[/i] bullets, high explosive rounds and electric discharge stunning rounds. 

The Lawgiver also has an advanced "[[DNA]] check" user verification system that only allows the owner of the gun to fire it.

title: su-37
body:
The [b]Sukhoi Su-37[/b] (NATO reporting name: [i]Flanker-F[/i]) is an experimental single-seat, supermaneuverable multirole [[jet]] fighter, designed by Sukhoi. 

A further development of the original [[Su-27]] "Flanker", it was modified from the first-generation [[Su-35]] (formerly "T10M") prototypes. The Su-37 features an upgraded avionic suite and fire-control system, but its most notable additions are the thrust-vectoring nozzles. Only two prototypes were converted.

During the Su-35 flight test programme, active controls during dogfighting maneuvers could not be attained. At the same time, Sukhoi was exploring the application of thrust-vectoring nozzles for fighter jets, giving it better dogfighting attributes. 

Throughout the entire program, the Su-37 demonstrated its potential to prospective operators at numerous air shows, performing maneuvers which were previously thought as impossible, among which was a 360° somersault. Despite its potential tactical advantage, the Su-37 did not enter production, and instead remained as a technology demonstrator for updated Su-27 family aircraft such as the export Su-30 and the Su-35BM.

title: su-33
body:
The [b]Sukhoi Su-33[/b] (Russian: Сухой Су-33; NATO reporting name: [i]Flanker-D[/i]) is an all-weather carrier-based air defense fighter designed by Sukhoi and manufactured by KnAAPO. 

A navalised derivative of the [[Su-27]], it was initially known as the Su-27K. When the fighter entered service in August 1998, its designation was changed to "Su-33". 

The Su-33 has strengthened structure, upgraded engines, a twin nose wheel, larger wing, and shortened tail stinger compared to the Su-27. It was replaced by the [[MiG-29]]K in 2009.

title: kimura_(mma)
body: Kimura (Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu), chicken wing/double wristlock (wrestling), or reverse keylock are terms used to specify a medial keylock known in judo as gyaku ude-garami (reverse arm entanglement) or simply as ude-garami. The application is similar to the americana, except that it is reversed. It needs some space behind the opponent to be effective, and can be applied from the side control or guard. Contrary to the americana, the opponent's wrist is grabbed with the hand on the same side, and the opposite arm is put behind the opponent's arm, again grabbing the attacker's wrist and forming a figure-four. By controlling the opponent's body and cranking the arm away from the attacker, pressure is put on the shoulder joint, and depending on the angle, also the elbow joint (in some variations the opponent's arm is brought behind their back, resulting in a finishing position resembling that of the hammerlock outlined below). The kimura was named after the judoka Masahiko Kimura, who used it to defeat one of the founders of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu, Hélio Gracie.

title: night_watch_series
body:
ナイトウォッチ三部作, lit. [i]Night Watch Trilogy[/i] is a light novel series written by "Kadono Kouhei":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kouhei_Kadono and illustrated by [[Nakazawa Kazuto]]. It was first published by Tokuma shoten in Tokuma Dual Bunko from 2000 to 2002. It is currently being re-published starting from 2012 by Seikaisha Bunko and titled as [[Night Watch series]]. The republished version is illustrated by [[Serori]].

It consisted three published volumes and one side-stories which is:

* Bokura ha Kokuu ni Yoru wo Miru
* Watashi ha Kyomu wo Tsuki ni Kiku
* Anata ha Kyojin to Hoshi ni Mau
* Tetsu Kamen wo Meguru Rongi (gaiden)

h4. Character

title: winchester_model_1897
body:
The Winchester Model 1897, also known as the Model 97, M97, or Trench Gun, was a pump-action [[shotgun]] with an external hammer and tube magazine manufactured by the Winchester Repeating Arms Company. An evolution of John Browning's Model 1893, over one million of these shotguns were produced from 1897 until 1957. It was offered in numerous barrel lengths and grades, chambered in 12 and 16 gauge, and as a solid frame or takedown.
